<br>
My character there was a mentalist which basically was the combination of a wizard, magician and enchanter.  I spent quite a bit of time deciding and came down to choosing between wizard and magician.  What made me choose wizard was all the stories about Merlin and how wizards should be masters of damage or in EQ language, direct damage.<br>
<br>
I will admit I see few wizards that are actual females.  And Vashanti you are correct.  Most women do tend to be in groups that I know that are wizards and less in soloing.  I for one hate soloing and feel if I am going to do that I might as well play an offline game.<br>
<br>
I do have a paladin but I hardly play my paladin like Xena <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   If I did I would be a warrior and not a paladin.<br>
<br>
So you might say it is all due to the fantasy books I read growing up that had me choose a wizard.  I never had played Dungeons and Dragons so this was a real learning experience all around.<br>
<br>
As to the question of men hitting on women.  Having played for over 3 years in EQ now I do not notice it as much at all.  But the first year or two it was exceptionally bad.  It still amuses me how some guys get all excited about what is pixels on a screen <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
And I know I am one of few on Bert that happens to have chosen an Erudite.  I see more male Erudite wizards than females.  Sort of way I seldom see many female high elf paladins (thats what I chose for my pally <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ).<br>
<br>
If I had to do it over again I would change nothing. <p>Alyssandra Blackthorne, 58 Wizard<BR>
